rorat._refObjectName: [CSL] HOT property drawer includes photos widget
rorat.Description:
As a travel agent I want to have the hotel photos available in the Hotel Search results so that I can quickly get the traveler's approval for the chosen hotel.

Details:
  • The widget look and functionality should be based on the Legacy hotels 'photos' widget
    • The miniature photo should be taken from the GetHotelAvail leading photo
    • There should be no photo count as the service should be called after modal opening
  • The hotel photos are available in the GetHotelDetails response. The service would have to be called on opening the modal and the response would have to be cached until the user opens the rates list or another drawer.
  • Hotel Details drawer should be extended with a separator and space for widgets. 
    • The new widget should be available in Graphic view as there's no Classic view for CSL 
  • The gallery solution should be similar to the Legacy hotels, but doesn't have to be identical
Performance considerations:
  • The GetHotelDetails service provides hotel description, photos and amenities. Amenity data is also available in the GetHotelAvail
  • The miniature in photos widget is also taken from GetHotelAvail
  • The widgets data could be loaded from a GetHotelDetails response requested on opening the drawer, or only on opening a widget. 
  • If the data is only requested on opening the widget, there can be no count on the Photos&videos widget

Only the Photos&Videos widget is included in this story (no photo count since the service should be called upon opening the widget):
rorat.Name: [CSL] HOT property drawer includes photos widget

rorat._refObjectName: [CSL] HOT property drawer includes amenities widget
rorat.Description:
As a travel agent I want to be able to show the client what value adds they will have at their chosen hotel so that they can make an informed decision.

Details:
  • The Amenities widget should be shown in the hotel availability results drawer
  • The Amenities data is available in the GetHotelContent response (the same as for the rest of the drawer widgets) or in the GetHotelAvail response
    • In the GetHotelContent request, the amenities information needs to be requested explicitly, or there will be no information sent back. (
      <Amenities>true</Amenities>)
    • The values are not available in the <RequestableAmenities> tag - those are covered in a separate story!
    • In the modal, the icons should be mapped by the OTA code of the amenity, and the icon label should be taken from the Description tag.
    • The Complimentary Indicator and the text it contains is not a part of this story.
  • Amenities should be presented with descriptions on the modal
    • The modal should accomodate the changing numbers of the amenity descriptions
  • The widget should be also available on the Hotel Details header drawer.
Acceptance criteria:
  • Search via CSL for a hotel e.g. in DFW 
  • Open a drawer 
  • There should be an Amenities widget, with  the amenities count

Performance considerations:
  • The GetHotelDetails service provides hotel description, photos and amenities. Amenity data is also available in the GetHotelAvail
  • The miniature in photos widget is also taken from GetHotelAvail
  • The widgets data could be loaded from a GetHotelDetails response requested on opening the drawer, or only on opening a widget. 
  • If the data is only requested on opening the widget, there can be no count on the Photos&videos widget

https://developer.sabre.com/docs/soap_apis/hotel/search/get_hotel_list









<Amenities>
<!-- Optional -->
<!-- Repeat Factor=1-unlimited -->
<!--
Code(Optional) - Numeric OTA code for the Amenity. Amenities in a Hotel are mapped to "HAC" OTA code
-->
<!--
Description (Optional) - Amenity Description. Ex- Bathtub, Computer
-->
<!--
ComplimentaryInd (Optional)- Indicates if the corresponding Amenity is complimentary or charged extra
-->
<!--
ComplimentaryInd='false', The given Amenity is charged extra
-->
<!--
ComplimentaryInd - When True the ComplimentaryInd attribute is not displayed in response. It is displayed in API response only if it is False
-->
<Amenity Code="215" Description="Exhibition/convention floor" ComplimentaryInd="false">Ask at reception for fees</Amenity>
</Amenities>
rorat.Name: [CSL] HOT property drawer includes amenities widget

rorat._refObjectName: [Tagging] As a User I want to receive tags for AirShopping with Shelves option enabled
rorat.Description:
The purpose of this story is to prepare air tagging decoration for air shopping response with shelves.

Backend:
When it comes to shelves, the structure of response is similar to wholesale fares, meaning the first shelves comes in "normal" AirItineraryPricingInfo and the rest in TPA_Extensions/AdditionalFares/AirItineraryPricingInfo.
There can be as much as 7 shelves, but we display on UI first 3 available. E.g. in there is no shelf="1" and shelf="3" for any itin, we display shelf=0, shelf=2 and shelf=4.

Frontend:
With tag2 there is simple case -> we display it for fare, for which it comes.
With tag1 decorate itin if tag1 is returned for at least one pricing option:
1/ if tag1 is returned for at least one fare, decorate itin with icon.
2/ if tag1 is returned for two fares and differ from eachother, display +1 next to the icon and concatenate tooltip (see design)
3/ if tag1 is returned for three fares and differ from eachother, display +2 next to the icon and concatenate tooltip
rorat.Name: [Tagging] As a User I want to receive tags for AirShopping with Shelves option enabled
rorat.c_SRWBusinessDescription: The purpose of this story is to decorate airshopping with shelves responses with tags. So far user was able to see tags only for standard airshopping response, right now also shelves are supported.

rorat._refObjectName: Focus is not set on Waitlist action when scan Availability is not available
rorat.Description:
CERT, R14I

Steps to reproduce

1. Search Availability for connecting flight
2. Go to the drawer and select different booking for each flight segment
3. Go to the Sell drop-down

Current Result:

When  Scan Availability is unavailable the focus is not set at all on the drop-down

Expected result:

Focus should be set on Waitlist action
rorat.Name: Focus is not set on Waitlist action when scan Availability is not available
rorat.c_SRWDEFECTINFORMATION: Defect already exists in last released version.

rorat._refObjectName: No branded fares when clicking book button from gui on air availability
rorat.Description:
Steps to reproduce:

1. 11NOVLASLAX'AA
2. Open first row and buy 1 y segment
3. Click book button

Expected results:
Branded fares achieved

Actual results:
No branded fares if no flights in PNR
What is more if you buy the same segment by command 01y1 Branded fares are achieved.
rorat.Name: No branded fares when clicking book button from gui on air availability

rorat._refObjectName: As a User I want to be ale to sell & Save Price for the option with free bag included
rorat.Description:
The options from the BFM reposne that was requested using Free Baggage qualifier need to be sold in a special manner.
This is because the Free Bag qualifier is not available in pricing, hence we need to use smart pricing (shop with fare basis code) qualifier -ZZ(farebasiscode), whenever the Brand id is not returned in the Shopping Response. sample command: WPS1*ZZFBC1¥S2*ZZFBC2
While constructing pricig command for the Save Price step ZZ qualilfier should be used on a single fare basis level taken from the BFM_RS of given option.
This should work similar to procing with BrandId.
 
Acceptance Criteria:
 
1. Check if fare chosen from shopping results (Base Fare, Taxes and Total fare) are the same as the fare stored in PQ after Sell&Save Price step
2. Check if Fare Basis code in the stored Priced Quote
rorat.Name: As a User I want to be ale to sell & Save Price for the option with free bag included
rorat.Notes:
To get this command from TPFC we need to fill field sws:OTA_AirPriceRQ/sws:PriceRequestInformation/sws:OptionalQualifiers/sws:PricingQualifiers/sws:SpecificFare with RPH and fare basis code.

5
